A man suspected of violently kidnapping a woman from her Milwaukie workplace and forcing her into a minivan has been named by police.

The suspect has been identified from CCTV footage as Kelly Vern Swoboda, 49, and is considered armed and dangerous.

The victim, in her mid-20s, was kidnapped from her place of employment on Highway 99 in the Portland suburb – but amazingly managed to leap from the vehicle she had been forced into as it was moving along.

