Clackamas County Sheriff's Office said that members of the public should immediately dial 911 if they spot Swoboda, who is at large.

The victim was working alone when the
 suspect walked into the business, physically assaulted her, and forced 
her outside and into a minivan, police said.

A statement described him as ‘an adult male around age 50, with gray hair, wire-rimmed glasses and a goatee or beard, wearing a dark navy-blue hooded jacket and driving a purple-colored minivan’.

The statement added: ‘Stranger-on-stranger abductions are extremely rare, and detectives are taking this case very seriously. This is an open and ongoing investigation.’

